Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.64,0:00:09.36,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Minori has never asked for my help.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.43,0:00:13.41,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,She's asked for advice or for teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.90,0:00:14.75,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,but...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.59,0:00:18.20,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,She has never asked me to help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.93,0:00:21.16,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.70,0:00:24.16,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Help us, please...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.93,0:00:26.33,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We have a casualty.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.68,0:00:28.32,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It's Rundel Haus.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.47,0:00:30.70,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,He is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.43,0:00:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one of the People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.84,0:02:05.27,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Call Karashin!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.49,0:02:08.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be in charge here for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.76,0:02:13.79,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,There are things even I can't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.61,0:02:18.65,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,No... In this irrational world,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.65,0:02:20.63,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,there aren't many things I {\i0}can{\i1} do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.85,0:02:22.69,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.96,0:02:27.86,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If Minori needs my help...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:35.05,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1862,1)}Contract
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.34,0:02:32.42,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.04,0:02:38.29,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.23,0:02:43.55,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Rundel Haus was fatally wounded \Nduring the defense of Choushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.03,0:02:47.16,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We've cast two revival spells, but they failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.57,0:02:50.76,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,However, he has a pulse, and he's still warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.07,0:02:53.56,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But he isn't waking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.76,0:02:56.19,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you, and who is with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.43,0:03:00.43,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It's Tohya, Isuzu, Serara, and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.43,0:03:02.05,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,And Rundel Haus.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.59,0:03:06.20,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We're near the crossroads, \Nat the center of Choushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.88,0:03:08.20,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Is it safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.58,0:03:10.26,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,There are no enemies in the vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.75,0:03:13.96,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But near the coast, there's still fighting going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.30,0:03:17.03,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know when the goblins will attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.03,0:03:20.55,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe, save Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.55,0:03:23.01,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who brought him here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.53,0:03:26.20,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I... It's my fault...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.15,0:03:29.29,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.67,0:03:33.79,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Tell Serara to cast a revival spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.79,0:03:34.48,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.19,0:03:36.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Stand by for 150 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.85,0:03:38.23,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya is to watch for enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.68,0:03:41.08,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Isuzu should use an MP-restoration song.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.61,0:03:44.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,After 150 seconds, you cast a revival spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.78,0:03:45.62,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.59,0:03:50.49,Default - italics,Re,0000,0000,0000,,The mystical energy that animates humans \Nand demi-humans is called the "spirit."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.29,0:03:54.99,SignA,Re,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1566,1)}Psyche
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.55,0:03:53.91,Default - italics,Re,0000,0000,0000,,Psyche is the energy that animates the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.91,0:03:55.54,Default - italics,Re,0000,0000,0000,,It affects things such as magic, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.36,0:03:58.49,Green HUD,Re,0000,0000,0000,,Psyche = Magic Points
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.00,0:03:58.50,Default - italics,Re,0000,0000,0000,,It is also called MP, magic points.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:01.84,SignA,,0000,0000,0000,,Anima
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.62,0:04:01.99,Default - flashback,Re,0000,0000,0000,,Anima is the energy that animates the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.86,0:04:08.00,Green HUD,Re,0000,0000,0000,,Anima = Hit Points
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.48,0:04:04.70,Default - flashback,Re,0000,0000,0000,,HP... Hit points.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.70,0:04:08.01,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,It is also the energy known as "ki."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.66,0:04:12.52,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,When someone is defeated in battle, \Nthe psyche and anima are split,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.89,0:04:15.68,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,and the flow of information from \Nbody to mind is severed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.37,0:04:19.72,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Then, the anima-dispersal begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.68,0:04:25.18,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Anima-dispersal is when the anima, \Nthe body, is dispersed and vanishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.94,0:04:29.53,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Revival magic gathers the anima dispersed \Ninto the surrounding atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.53,0:04:31.45,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and reconstructs it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.58,0:04:34.25,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Regan hypothesized that
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.25,0:04:37.76,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,revival magic would work on People of the \NLand, if used immediately after death.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.64,0:04:43.35,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If it's strengthening his pulse, \Nhis body was successfully restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.34,0:04:46.76,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But if he hasn't woken up,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.49,0:04:52.02,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,his psyche, the energy that powers his mind, \Nhas begun to disperse, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.36,0:04:56.77,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,When the body disperses, so does the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.96,0:05:00.96,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And when the body is completely gone,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.96,0:05:04.55,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,the mind has nowhere to return, \Nmaking revival impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.38,0:05:07.67,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, People of the Land die.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.86,0:05:13.25,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,An adventurer's body is automatically \Nrestored at the Cathedral,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.25,0:05:17.29,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,and the psyche, or mind, \Nis connected to it, so they revive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:20.41,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,150 seconds have passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.41,0:05:22.44,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm casting a revival spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.44,0:05:25.33,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,In another 150 seconds, use Serara's again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.35,0:05:27.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on my way now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.18,0:05:30.75,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Keep alternating for another eight minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.75,0:05:31.56,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.21,0:05:35.54,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, all we can do is to stop \Nthe body from being destroyed...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.39,0:05:38.49,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.83,0:05:41.57,Default - flashback,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it your job to think, Shiro?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.63,0:05:44.57,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.03,0:05:49.01,Default - flashback,S,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't mean I can just take you \Nto see the midnight sun in Iceland—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.01,0:05:51.83,Default - flashback,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,But I want to see it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.68,0:05:54.45,Default - flashback,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a dreamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:05:56.83,Default - flashback,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,And you make my dreams come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.83,0:05:57.80,Default - flashback,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.28,0:06:00.52,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But still...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.82,0:06:07.39,Default - flashback,Re,0000,0000,0000,,I specialize in the study of world-class magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.98,0:06:11.91,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Magic that alters the rules of the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.90,0:06:15.56,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki, take the reins!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.73,0:06:39.64,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Milord...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.24,0:06:43.07,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought the report.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.97,0:06:44.89,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.20,0:06:48.77,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,What am I...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.97,0:06:54.86,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,How goes the battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.58,0:06:59.86,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to have grown quite popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:02.28,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,She looked at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.64,0:07:04.27,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Northerner girls are total angels!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.28,0:07:04.27,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta take a picture... Wait, I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.27,0:07:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.34,0:07:09.79,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Dire wolves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.37,0:07:12.11,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Probably the huge race.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.11,0:07:14.84,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,The Goblin King?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.42,0:07:18.06,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,He won't leave Seventh Fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.59,0:07:21.70,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, it's the Goblin General's forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.70,0:07:22.96,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.61,0:07:27.88,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,We can clean up their nest later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.35,0:07:32.97,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's murder every single \None of the bastards in Zantleaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.92,0:07:40.03,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if I can really do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.67,0:07:43.10,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And even if it does work...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.70,0:07:44.54,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.95,0:07:45.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Akatsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.25,0:07:50.18,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.63,0:07:53.07,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,The Ocypete has reached Choushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.55,0:07:56.99,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But the sahuagin are making landing difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.39,0:07:59.10,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,They've begun combat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.24,0:08:03.00,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone! Reinforcements are here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.51,0:08:07.00,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Just a bit more! Just hang on a bit more!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.79,0:08:10.01,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki, watch our surroundings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.01,0:08:11.00,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.12,0:08:14.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Move everyone away from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.19,0:08:18.55,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let anyone near, players or monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.55,0:08:19.52,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Leave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.25,0:08:30.25,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.25,0:08:31.41,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.95,0:08:33.78,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Is this him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.25,0:08:35.18,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.18,0:08:37.03,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,This is Rundel Haus.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.85,0:08:43.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Minori, add me to your party.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.92,0:08:44.74,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.39,0:08:46.58,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're Isuzu, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.93,0:08:49.66,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Keep casting Meditation Nocturne.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.66,0:08:51.09,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.56,0:08:53.50,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to use a new magic spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.77,0:08:56.41,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Tell no one about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.85,0:08:58.47,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,A new magic spell?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.96,0:09:02.73,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't agree to that, either give up or leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.56,0:09:08.36,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.01,0:09:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.42,0:09:21.12,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an5}Skills > Shiroe
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.36,0:09:21.12,HUD1,S,0000,0000,0000,,Undo\NOver-runner\NMana-channeling
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.89,0:09:13.25,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Mana-channeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.79,0:09:15.37,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.76,0:09:21.12,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,It's an enchanter's skill that absorbs MP from \Nall party members and returns it equally.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.88,0:09:23.62,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.12,0:09:31.38,HUD1,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Tohya                                 Minori                     Isuzu
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.12,0:09:31.38,HUD1,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,{\an3}Serara                               Shiroe                       Rundel Haus Code
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.19,0:09:34.26,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Psyche is the vessel of the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.26,0:09:36.88,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,and it is also MP...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.32,0:09:38.15,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.56,0:09:45.31,HUD1,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,{\an9}Rundel Haus Code
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.11,0:09:51.36,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Minori, use a revival spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.71,0:09:53.06,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Serara, continuous healing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.51,0:09:54.34,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.42,0:10:00.26,Default - italics,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Rundel Haus's MP, his mind, is now \Nactive, but he's still unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.69,0:10:03.37,Default - italics,Se,0000,0000,0000,,So the link between anima and psyche,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.37,0:10:05.94,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,his body and mind, is still cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.86,0:10:09.80,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's a race against time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.63,0:10:13.32,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Revival Incense...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.71,0:10:19.23,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,This will turn a dead ally or creature \Ninto a zombie for three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.65,0:10:25.33,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use it to forcibly connect his \Nbody and mind for three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.69,0:10:32.64,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.32,0:10:34.45,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.45,0:10:35.57,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.42,0:10:44.14,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.53,0:10:45.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.35,0:10:50.45,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Isuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.07,0:10:52.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.64,0:10:58.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.37,0:11:02.09,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I died, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.14,0:11:05.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look so sad, everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.67,0:11:11.20,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Dying is a natural consequence of battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.75,0:11:14.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Natural?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.49,0:11:18.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, I wanted to be an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.23,0:11:22.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame Miss Isuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.93,0:11:25.55,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It was I who begged her to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.91,0:11:27.12,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.47,0:11:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.19,0:11:32.80,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it, too, but I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.80,0:11:34.13,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.49,0:11:35.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minori...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.76,0:11:38.88,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Miss Minori.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.21,0:11:40.68,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let it bother you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.45,0:11:43.26,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, I will let it bother me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.75,0:11:46.11,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Rundel Haus Code,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.89,0:11:51.52,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse to allow anyone who gives up so \Neasily to call himself an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.99,0:11:53.77,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's not nearly enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.47,0:11:58.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What have you learned?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.91,0:12:03.89,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What you acquired in the dungeon \Nwas not strategy and tactics,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.89,0:12:08.18,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,but the resolve to survive, and the \Nfortitude to do whatever it takes to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.18,0:12:09.85,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.54,0:12:11.66,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.97,0:12:16.17,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Your resolve is sorely lacking, Rundel Haus!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.38,0:12:18.92,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do you want me to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.51,0:12:21.42,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.93,0:12:23.53,Default,MiSe,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.53,0:12:24.93,Default,MiSe,0000,0000,0000,,A contract?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.61,0:12:26.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,A contract.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.18,0:12:30.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe, leader of the guild Log Horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.03,0:12:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,establishes the following contract \Nwith Rundel Haus Code.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.23,0:12:43.26,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,1. Effective as of the date and time at which \NRundel Haus Code signs this document,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.26,0:12:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe accepts him as a member \Nof the guild Log Horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.81,0:12:53.03,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,2. As a member of the guild Log Horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.03,0:12:57.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rundel Haus Code will fulfill his missions \Nin a manner befitting his position.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.69,0:13:01.49,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,3. Log Horizon will provide Rundel Haus Code
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.49,0:13:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all necessary support required for his missions,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.44,0:13:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the greatest extent acceptable to both parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.31,0:13:13.43,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,This includes bestowing the status of "adventurer."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.79,0:13:21.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,4. This contract is signed in the spirit of mutual \Nrespect and agreement between both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.74,0:13:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything either party acquires, \Nfor the contract's duration,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.20,0:13:28.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,remains theirs, even in the event \Nthat the contract is nullified.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.15,0:13:34.37,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Two copies of this contract will \Nbe signed by both parties,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.85,0:13:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and each party will retain a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.25,0:13:40.30,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.40,0:13:46.82,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A new kind of magic that didn't exist \Nwhen{\i0} Elder Tale {\i1}was a game! {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.05,0:13:50.97,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The secret to cooking that Chief Nyanta told us...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.99,0:13:54.51,HUD Big,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(424,1)}Nyanta \N{\fs24}Race/ Cat-man \NSwashbuckler, Lv. 90
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.64,0:13:55.17,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,If you cook it yourself, rather than \Nrelying on the cooking command,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.62,0:13:58.06,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,you can make tasty food, \Nprovided your skill level is high enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.98,0:14:02.16,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,I realized that this applied \Nto more than cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.02,0:14:04.23,SignD,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(696,1)}This is a {\c&H535683&}steam engine!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.14,0:14:03.92,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.56,0:14:09.62,Default - flashback,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,You're researching whether you can \Ndo something with the scribe skill?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.54,0:14:14.23,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,The Fairy King's paper, made from \Nthe best ingredients in the game,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.06,0:14:16.60,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,ink from the Time Dragon's eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.67,0:14:22.77,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,and a contract written by a level-90 scribe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.17,0:14:27.84,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what effect this magic \Nwill have on this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.21,0:14:30.04,Default - italics,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.15,0:14:32.76,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,I've added my signature.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.25,0:14:34.60,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Now it only needs yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.27,0:14:39.81,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,An adventurer...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.95,0:14:42.90,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,This contract contains an element of risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.90,0:14:47.24,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be a different kind of being \Nthan you've been until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.16,0:14:51.91,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,We adventurers are still new to \Nthis world, and we don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.91,0:14:54.90,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,what we'll be caught up in from here on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.71,0:14:59.79,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think adventurers garner all \Nthe glory you believe them to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.36,0:15:02.16,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,What I want is to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.11,0:15:05.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.73,0:15:08.89,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,If I can save people who need my help,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.52,0:15:11.47,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about the details...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.65,0:15:15.21,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.57,0:15:18.49,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be an adventurer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.02,0:15:25.16,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.96,0:15:29.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,I'll write it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.66,0:16:08.32,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You need to die once, Rundel Haus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.44,0:16:19.70,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You'll come back to life at the Cathedral.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.42,0:17:39.41,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,A summoned creature, restricted to \Ncharacters level 86 and above...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.93,0:17:40.99,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,The phoenix.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.29,0:18:06.20,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then... Let's tear them apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.86,0:18:26.98,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,The main dish is finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.35,0:18:31.51,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,We'll leave the rest to the \Nstrategic headquarters cordon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.22,0:18:49.33,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Marie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.30,0:18:59.07,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.41,0:19:00.91,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.91,0:19:02.61,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm bushed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.42,0:19:13.37,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Naotsugu...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.37,0:19:14.46,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.06,0:19:17.45,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,We did good, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.01,0:19:19.43,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.81,0:19:22.51,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,We saved the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.39,0:19:33.08,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe, why did you say that to Rundel Haus?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.68,0:19:34.83,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Say what?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.83,0:19:37.62,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,About adventurers, and resolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.12,0:19:42.74,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,"Adventurers"...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.17,0:19:46.39,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,When {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0} was just a game,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.39,0:19:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that was just a word we used for players.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.34,0:19:53.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But now, I think it's something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.01,0:19:57.84,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's the name for my companions,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.23,0:20:01.01,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,those who travel the world with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.74,0:20:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to find a dawn no one has ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.99,0:20:26.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.83,0:20:28.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.81,0:20:31.44,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Cathedral?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.71,0:20:37.78,HUD Big,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs24}Sub Class: Adventurer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.71,0:20:37.78,HUD Big,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs24\an6}Rundel Haus Code \N{\fs22}Race/ Human \NSorcerer, Lv. 25 \NLog Horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.54,0:20:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Adventurer"!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.78,0:20:40.95,HUD1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs24}Sub Class: Adventurer \N{\fs20}Class Abilities \NCan Revive at Cathedral \NFriend List \NEXP Bonus \NBank Vault \NDetailed Status
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.44,0:20:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.28,0:20:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.32,0:20:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an adventurer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.63,0:20:48.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just the same as...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.38,0:20:51.45,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.66,0:20:56.99,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,M-Miss Isuzu...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.82,0:21:00.91,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.36,0:21:02.93,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.93,0:21:05.07,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You used a return spell to come back?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.07,0:21:08.85,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,What if you had died, \Ndoing something that reckless?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.85,0:21:10.08,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.08,0:21:12.02,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.57,0:21:14.40,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, you have to be willing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.40,0:21:17.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to sacrifice your life for duty, Miss Isuzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.42,0:21:20.21,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If I tell you to wait, you wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.54,0:21:21.96,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,That's not fair...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.24,0:21:22.97,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,You wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.46,0:21:27.57,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.31,0:21:31.32,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I made you worry...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.09,0:21:37.10,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I shouldn't have done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.96,0:21:40.57,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.89,0:21:44.19,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I w-won't do it again—
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.02,0:21:47.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.04,0:21:50.70,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! I'll do what you say, Miss Isuzu!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.13,0:21:54.25,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.25,0:21:55.75,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.75,0:21:57.13,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I swear to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.13,0:22:00.29,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,And you're going to tell me \Nabout when you were a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.29,0:22:02.19,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Why? It isn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.96,0:22:07.52,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,F-Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.91,0:22:09.03,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.03,0:22:10.51,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,If you do crazy things like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.51,0:22:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you won't survive, no matter \Nhow many lives you have!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.01,0:22:15.27,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I'll remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.27,0:22:16.52,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Then give me your paw!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.28,0:22:17.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.92,0:24:06.05,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,The battle has ended.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.40,0:24:09.57,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Eastal and the Round Table \Ntake a new step forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.57,0:24:12.30,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,To celebrate their victory, a ball is held.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.30,0:24:16.88,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,But Akatsuki is gloomy, amidst the cheer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.21,0:24:20.25,Default,Preview,0000,0000,0000,,Fall is coming to the town of Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.89,0:24:23.12,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,Next time: The Two of Us Shall Waltz.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.89,0:24:29.03,Title,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,The Two of Us Shall Waltz
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.54,0:24:25.78,Default,Next time,0000,0000,0000,,We will change the world.
